metadata.title: Embraer Phenom 300
aws::graph::propositions: Embraer Phenom 300 Upgrade Announcement and Certification
Embraer announced a package of upgrades to the Phenom 300 on 31 January 2020.
The upgrades increased the Phenom 300's maximum speed from Mach 0.78 to Mach 0.80.
The maximum speed increase represented a change from 446 to 464 knots.
The maximum speed increase represented a change from 826 to 859 km/h.
The maximum speed increase represented a change from 513 to 534 mph.
The upgrades expanded the Phenom 300's endurance from 1,992 to 2,010 nautical miles.
The endurance increase represented a change from 3,689 to 3,723 kilometers.
The endurance increase represented a change from 2,292 to 2,313 miles.
The upgrades raised the Phenom 300's rated engine thrust from 3,360 to 3,478 lbf.
The engine thrust increase represented a change from 14.95 to 15.47 kN.
The improved PW535E1 turbofan engines were adopted in the Phenom 300 upgrade.
The Phenom 300E received triple certification during March 2020.
By early 2023, the Phenom 300E's equipped price was US$10.995 million.

text: On 31 January 2020, Embraer announced that it was implementing a package of upgrades to the Phenom 300; resulting changes included the maximum speed being increased from Mach 0.78 to 0.80 (446 to 464 kn, 826 to 859 km/h, 513 to 534 mph), expanded endurance from 1,992 to 2,010 nmi (3,689 to 3,723 km; 2,292 to 2,313 mi), and the rated engine thrust being raised from 3,360 to 3,478 lbf (14.95 to 15.47 kN) via the adoption of improved PW535E1 turbofan engines. During March 2020, the Phenom 300E received triple certification from Brazils ANAC, the FAA, and EASA. By early 2023, the aircraft's equipped price was US$10.995 million.
